<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1886-08-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1886-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="336" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d336">
                    <head>No. 332.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Jackson</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1886-08-13"><hi rend="italic">August</hi> 13, 1886</date>.
                            (Received August 13.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Jackson informs Mr. Bayard that the government of Coahuila asserts that
                        Arresures was by law a Mexican and a fugitive from justice; and that after
                        he had been extradited, and while he was being conducted to court, he took
                        flight, and, in the pursuit that followed, was killed.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>